<title>JAPAN: Japan to seek forex stability with key nations-MOF.</title>
<headline>Japan to seek forex stability with key nations-MOF.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-01-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Finance Minister Hiroshi Mitsuzuka said on Wednesday that Japan would continue to seek currency stability in cooperation with other major industrial nations.  </p>
<p>In a speech to parliament's finance committee, Mitsuzuka said: &quot;Regarding foreign exchange rates, we will continue to seek stability in cooperation with other major industrial nations.&quot;</p>
<p>He also said the ministry would keep a close watch on Tokyo stock price movements.</p>
